The paper deals with video anomaly detection and localization using deep learning techniques. The primary focus is on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques, which are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of variational autoencoders (AI), which is another possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses motion analysis (MM) and energy-based methods (NE) to score the anomaly of image test patches.
